#only used in syt_check
get_i = function(a,k,n){
  return(ifelse(length(a)<k,n,a[k]))
}

syt_check = function(pl){
  row_check = map(pl,~diff(.x)>0)%>% unlist() %>% all()
  if(!row_check) return(F)
  l = map(pl,length)%>% unlist()
  n = sum(l)
  l_check = all(diff(l) <= 0)
  if(!l_check) return(F)
  for(i in 1:l[1]){
    col = imap(pl,~get_i(.x,i,n+.y)) %>% unlist()
    if(!all(diff(col)>0)) return(F)
  }
  return(T)
}
# pos is to determine the position of z in a, return the position to be bumped
# a is always sorted, so binary search is used.
pos = function(z,a){
  n = length(a)
  if(n == 0) return(1)
  if(n == 1){
    if(z > a[1]) return(2)
    return(1)
  }
  i = round((1+n)/2)
  if(z>a[i]){
    if(i == n) return(n+1)
    p = i+pos(z,a[(i+1):n])
  }else{
    p = pos(z,a[1:(i-1)])
  }
  return(p)
}

#insert z into a, append or bump, it is build on pos
insert_array = function(z,a){
  zi = pos(z,a)
  tmp = -1
  if(zi > length(a)) {
    a = c(a,z)
  }else{
    tmp = a[zi]
    a[zi] = z
  }
  return(list(bump = tmp,array = a))
}


#insert z into a tableaux list, it is build on insert_array
# it handles the bumping by creating new box and insert into lower rows
#xy: pl[[y]][x] == z
# should include ql in this function
insert_list = function(z,pl){
  n = length(pl)
  xy = c(0,0)
  if(n == 0){
    pl = c(pl,list(z))
    xy = c(1,1)
  }else{
    for(i in 1:n){
      u = insert_array(z,pl[[i]])
      pl[[i]] = u$array
      if(u$bump == -1){
        z = u$bump
        break
      }else{
        z = u$bump
      }
    }
    
    if(z != -1){
      pl = c(pl,list(z))
      xy = c(1,length(pl))
    }else{
      xy = c(length(pl[[i]]),i)
    }
  }
  
  return(list(pl = pl,xy = xy))
}

#as the insert list record the xy (in order) instead of q, this function
#xys is a list, the box coordinators and depth is the creation time
xy2q = function(xys){
  n = length(xys)
  ql = list()
  ys = map(xys,~.x[2]) %>% unlist()
  xs = map(xys,~.x[1]) %>% unlist()
  df = data.frame(ys,xs) %>% group_by(ys)%>% summarise(mx = max(xs))%>% arrange(ys)
  for(i in 1:max(ys)){
    ql = c(ql,list(rep(0,df$mx[i])))
  }
  for(i in 1:n){
    ql[[ys[i]]][xs[i]] = i
  }
  return(ql)
}

#this function reverse xy2q
q2xy = function(ql){
  mx = map(ql,length) %>% unlist()
  my = length(ql)
  n = sum(mx)
  xyis = list()
  for(i in 1:my){
    for(j in 1:mx[i]){
      xyis = c(xyis,list(c(i = ql[[i]][j],x = j,y=i)))
    }
  }
  xyi.m = map_df(xyis,~.x) %>% arrange(i) %>% as.matrix()
  xys = rep(list(0),n)
  for(i in 1:n){
    a =xyi.m[i,2:3]
    names(a) = c()
    xys[[i]] = a
  }
  return(xys)
}

#s = sample.int(6)
rs_bump_s2pq = function(s){
  pl = list()
  xys = list()
  for(z in s){
    sth = insert_list(z,pl)
    pl = sth$pl
    xys = c(xys,list(sth$xy))
  }
  ql = xy2q(xys)
  return(list(pl = pl,ql = ql,xys = xys))
}


rs_bump_pq2s= function(pl,ql){
  n = length(pl)
  s = rep(0,n)
  if(syt_check(pl) &syt_check(ql)){
    xys = q2xy(ql)
    n = length(xys)
    for(i in n:1){
      xy = xys[[i]]
      x = xy[1]
      y = xy[2]
      z = pl[[y]][x]
      pl[[y]] = pl[[y]][-x]
      if(y > 1){
        for(yi in (y-1):1){
          x = pos(z,pl[[yi]])
          tmp = pl[[yi]][x-1]
          pl[[yi]][x-1] = z
          z = tmp
        }      
      }
      s[i] = z
    }
  }
  return(s)
}
shift_cross = function(df){
  #df = data.frame(x = x, y =y)
  x = df %>% pull(x)
  y = df %>% pull(y)
   ind = sort.int(x,index.return =T)
   x = x[ind$ix]
   y = y[ind$ix]
  x = x[-1]
  y = y[-length(y)]
  return(data.frame(x = x, y = y))
}

edge_points = function(x,y){

    l = length(x)
    ii = c()
    for(i in 1:l){
      x0 = x[i]
      y0 = y[i]
       if(!any(x < x0 & y < y0)){
         ii = c(ii,i)
       }
    }
    return(ii)
}

xy2xy = function(x,y){
  l = length(x)
  k = 0
  ps = data.frame()
  while(l>0){
    k = k +1
    ii = edge_points(x,y)
    ps = rbind(ps,data.frame(x = x[ii],y = y[ii],k = k))
    x = x[-ii]
    y = y[-ii]
    l = length(x)
  }
  
  pss = ps %>% nest(d = c(x,y)) %>% mutate(d = map(d,shift_cross)) %>% unnest(d)
  x = pss %>% pull(x)
  y = pss %>% pull(y)
  return(list(ps = ps, pss = pss, x = x, y = y))
}

shadow_lines = function(s){
  x = seq_along(s)
  y = s
  l = length(x)
  ps = data.frame()
  while(l>0){
    tmp = xy2xy(x,y)
    x = tmp$x
    y = tmp$y
    tmp = tmp$ps
    tmp$l = l
    ps = rbind(ps,tmp)
    l = length(x)
  }
  return(ps)
}
shadow_line_pq = function(pl,ql){
  df = data.frame()
  if(syt_check(pl) &syt_check(ql)){
    l = map_int(pl,length)
    i = imap(l,~rep(.y,.x)) %>% unlist()
    x = ql %>% unlist()
    y = pl %>% unlist()
    df = data.frame(x = x, y = y,l =i)

    lz = max(df$l)
    while(lz>1){
      df_c = df %>% filter(l == lz) %>% arrange(-y)
      df_p = df %>% filter(l == lz-1) %>% arrange(-x)
      xy_ns = data.frame()
      k = dim(df_c)[1]
      for(ii in 1:k){
        xc = df_c[ii,"x"]
        yc = df_c[ii,"y"]       
        jj = which.max(df_p$x < xc & df_p$y < yc)
        xp = df_p[jj, "x"]
        yp = df_p[jj, "y"]

        xy_n = data.frame(x = c(xp,xc), y = c(yc,yp))# make_edge(xp,yp,xc,yc)
        xy_n$l = lz-1
        df_p = df_p[-jj,]
        df_p = rbind(df_p, xy_n)%>% arrange(-x)
      }
      
      df = df %>% filter(l != lz-1) %>% rbind(xy_ns,df_p )#%>% select(-s))
      df %>%arrange(l)%>% ggplot()+shadow_plot()
      lz = lz -1
    }
    
    #df$l = as.numeric(df$l)
  }
  return(df)
}
#zl = rep(list(rep(0,3)),3)
hook_numbers = function(pl){
  n = length(pl)
  l = map_int(pl,length)
  x = map(l,~seq(.x,1))
  y = map(l,~rep(0,.x))
  for(i in (n-1):1){
    b = y[[i+1]]
    for(j in seq_along(b)){
      y[[i]][j] = 1+b[j]
    }
  }
  h = map2(x,y, ~.x+.y)
}

#zl = rep(list(rep(0,3)),3) => 42
syt_number = function(pl){
  h = hook_numbers(pl)
  hf = prod(map_int(h,prod))
  n = sum(map_int(pl,length))
  syt_n = factorial(n)/hf
  return(syt_n)
}
#it use n, but not specify any where, n is the length of s, the permutation
shadow_plot = function(){
  list(geom_point(aes(x = x, y = y,color = factor(l)),size = 3),
       geom_segment(aes(x = x,xend = n+1,y = y,yend = y,color = factor(l))),
       geom_segment(aes(x = x,xend = x,y = y,yend = n+1,color = factor(l))))
}

show_box = function(pl){
  xys = q2xy(pl)
  xys.df = map_df(xys,~{names(.x)= c("x","y"); return(.x)})
  v = c()
  n = dim(xys.df)[1]
  for(i in 1:n){
    v = c(v,pl[[xys.df$y[i]]][xys.df$x[i]])
  }
  xys.df$v = v
  h = 0.5
  p = xys.df %>% ggplot(aes(x = x, y = y ))+
    geom_rect(aes(xmin = x-h, xmax = x+h, ymin = y-h, ymax = y+h),fill = "grey90",color = "black")+
    geom_text(aes(label = v),size = 5)+theme_void()+
    scale_y_reverse()+coord_equal()
 # print(p)
  return(p)
}

#modified from https://github.com/stla/syt/blob/master/R/RSK.R
bump <- function(P, Q, e, i){
  if(length(P)==0L) return(list(P=list(e), Q=list(i)))
  p <- P[[1L]]
  if(e >= p[length(p)]){ #with eq -jx
    P[[1L]] <- c(p, e)
    Q[[1L]] <- c(Q[[1L]], i)
    return(list(P=P, Q=Q))
  }else{
    j <- which.min(p <= e) #with eq -jx
    w <- p[j]
    P[[1L]][j] <- e
    b <- bump(P[-1L], Q[-1L], w, i)
    return(list(P=c(P[1L], b$P), Q=c(Q[1L], b$Q)))
  }
}

#I add the index, see if it work for generalized two-line array
RSK <- function(sigma, index=seq_along(sigma)){
  # if(!setequal(sigma,seq_along(sigma))){
  #   stop("`sigma` is not a permutation", call. = FALSE)
  # }
  sigma <- as.integer(sigma)
  out <- bump(list(), list(), sigma[1L], index[1L]) #wrap into index  -jx
  for(i in seq_along(sigma)[-1L]){
    out <- bump(out$P, out$Q, sigma[i], index[i]) #wrap into index  -jx
  }
  return(out)
}
#https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robinson%E2%80%93Schensted%E2%80%93Knuth_correspondence
index = c(2,2,3,4,5,6,6,8)
